⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Mr. Putnam
node WIZ · WIZ · ⟦Mr. Putnam:WIZ:60e0c3⟧

WHO   — Mr. Putnam — the child-tracking bounty hunter
WHAT  — The comic menace: an adult who treats lost children as a paycheck, always one diner booth behind.
WHERE — WIZ · The Wizard (1989)  Framework inputs: The Wizard (1989, dir. Todd Holland, Universal); verified cast & Nintendo history  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the quest needs a villain who's all appetite and no heart — Putnam is the grown-up who forgot how to be a kid.
HOW   — By tracking, cornering, and grabbing — and by being outsmarted by children every time.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Finding lost kids is a business. And business, right now, is good.

